events.description: The Lateran Council ends by condemning the Council of Hieria and anathematizing its iconoclastic rulings.
events.html: • 769 – The Lateran Council ends by condemning the Council of Hieria and anathematizing its iconoclastic rulings.[1]

events.description: Bari, the last Byzantine possession in southern Italy, is surrendered to Robert Guiscard.
events.html: • 1071 – Bari, the last Byzantine possession in southern Italy, is surrendered to Robert Guiscard.[2]

events.description: Battle of Formigny: Toward the end of the Hundred Years' War, the French attack and nearly annihilate English forces, ending English domination in Northern France.
events.html: • 1450 – Battle of Formigny: Toward the end of the Hundred Years' War, the French attack and nearly annihilate English forces, ending English domination in Northern France.[3]

events.description: Battle of Rain: Swedes under Gustavus Adolphus defeat the Holy Roman Empire during the Thirty Years' War.
events.html: • 1632 – Battle of Rain: Swedes under Gustavus Adolphus defeat the Holy Roman Empire during the Thirty Years' War.[4]

events.description: Irish Confederate Wars: A Confederate Irish militia is routed in the Battle of Kilrush when it attempts to halt the progress of a Royalist Army.
events.html: • 1642 – Irish Confederate Wars: A Confederate Irish militia is routed in the Battle of Kilrush when it attempts to halt the progress of a Royalist Army.[5]

events.description: The Pocotaligo Massacre triggers the start of the Yamasee War in colonial South Carolina.
events.html: • 1715 – The Pocotaligo Massacre triggers the start of the Yamasee War in colonial South Carolina.[6]

events.description: Foundation of the short-lived Kingdom of Corsica.
events.html: • 1736 – Foundation of the short-lived Kingdom of Corsica.

events.description: Serse, an Italian opera by George Frideric Handel, receives its premiere performance in London, England.
events.html: • 1738 – Serse, an Italian opera by George Frideric Handel, receives its premiere performance in London, England.[7]

events.description: Samuel Johnson's A Dictionary of the English Language is published in London.
events.html: • 1755 – Samuel Johnson's A Dictionary of the English Language is published in London.[8]

entities.name: A Dictionary of the English Language

events.description: Thomas Hopkins Gallaudet and Laurent Clerc found the American School for the Deaf (then called the Connecticut Asylum for the Education and Instruction of Deaf and Dumb Persons), the first American school for deaf students, in Hartford, Connecticut.
events.html: • 1817 – Thomas Hopkins Gallaudet and Laurent Clerc found the American School for the Deaf (then called the Connecticut Asylum for the Education and Instruction of Deaf and Dumb Persons), the first American school for deaf students, in Hartford, Connecticut.[9]

events.description: President Abraham Lincoln calls for 75,000 volunteers to quell the insurrection that soon became the American Civil War.
events.html: • 1861 – President Abraham Lincoln calls for 75,000 volunteers to quell the insurrection that soon became the American Civil War.[10]

events.description: President Abraham Lincoln dies after being shot the previous evening by actor John Wilkes Booth. Three hours later, Vice President Andrew Johnson is sworn in as president.
events.html: • 1865 – President Abraham Lincoln dies after being shot the previous evening by actor John Wilkes Booth.[11] Three hours later, Vice President Andrew Johnson is sworn in as president.[12]

events.description: The General Electric Company is formed.
events.html: • 1892 – The General Electric Company is formed.[13]

events.description: Closing ceremony of the Games of the I Olympiad in Athens, Greece.
events.html: • 1896 – Closing ceremony of the Games of the I Olympiad in Athens, Greece.[14]

events.description: Philippine–American War: Filipino guerrillas launch a surprise attack on U.S. infantry and begin a four-day siege of Catubig, Philippines.
events.html: • 1900 – Philippine–American War: Filipino guerrillas launch a surprise attack on U.S. infantry and begin a four-day siege of Catubig, Philippines.[15]

events.description: The British passenger liner RMS Titanic sinks in the North Atlantic at 2:20 a.m., two hours and forty minutes after hitting an iceberg. Only 710 of 2,224 passengers and crew on board survive.
events.html: • 1912 – The British passenger liner RMS Titanic sinks in the North Atlantic at 2:20 a.m., two hours and forty minutes after hitting an iceberg. Only 710 of 2,224 passengers and crew on board survive.

events.description: Two security guards are murdered during a robbery in South Braintree, Massachusetts. Anarchists Sacco and Vanzetti would be convicted of and executed for the crime, amid much controversy.
events.html: • 1920 – Two security guards are murdered during a robbery in South Braintree, Massachusetts. Anarchists Sacco and Vanzetti would be convicted of and executed for the crime, amid much controversy.

events.description: U.S. Senator John B. Kendrick of Wyoming introduces a resolution calling for an investigation of a secret land deal, which leads to the discovery of the Teapot Dome scandal.
events.html: • 1922 – U.S. Senator John B. Kendrick of Wyoming introduces a resolution calling for an investigation of a secret land deal, which leads to the discovery of the Teapot Dome scandal.

events.description: Insulin becomes generally available for use by people with diabetes.
events.html: • 1923 – Insulin becomes generally available for use by people with diabetes.

events.description: Racially motivated Nihon Shōgakkō fire lit by a serial arsonist kills 10 children in Sacramento, California.
events.html: • 1923 – Racially motivated Nihon Shōgakkō fire lit by a serial arsonist kills 10 children in Sacramento, California.[16]

events.description: First day of the Arab revolt in Mandatory Palestine.
events.html: • 1936 – First day of the Arab revolt in Mandatory Palestine.

events.description: In the Belfast Blitz, two hundred bombers of the German Luftwaffe attack Belfast, killing around one thousand people.
events.html: • 1941 – In the Belfast Blitz, two hundred bombers of the German Luftwaffe attack Belfast, killing around one thousand people.

events.description: The George Cross is awarded "to the island fortress of Malta" by King George VI.
events.html: • 1942 – The George Cross is awarded "to the island fortress of Malta" by King George VI.

entities.name: Award of the George Cross to Malta

events.description: Bergen-Belsen concentration camp is liberated.
events.html: • 1945 – Bergen-Belsen concentration camp is liberated.

events.description: Jackie Robinson debuts for the Brooklyn Dodgers, breaking baseball's color line.
events.html: • 1947 – Jackie Robinson debuts for the Brooklyn Dodgers, breaking baseball's color line.

events.description: First flight of the Boeing B-52 Stratofortress.
events.html: • 1952 – First flight of the Boeing B-52 Stratofortress.

events.description: McDonald's restaurant dates its founding to the opening of a franchised restaurant by Ray Kroc, in Des Plaines, Illinois.
events.html: • 1955 – McDonald's restaurant dates its founding to the opening of a franchised restaurant by Ray Kroc, in Des Plaines, Illinois.

events.description: At Shaw University in Raleigh, North Carolina, Ella Baker leads a conference that results in the creation of the Student Nonviolent Coordinating Committee, one of the principal organizations of the civil rights movement in the 1960s.
events.html: • 1960 – At Shaw University in Raleigh, North Carolina, Ella Baker leads a conference that results in the creation of the Student Nonviolent Coordinating Committee, one of the principal organizations of the civil rights movement in the 1960s.

events.description: The EC-121 shootdown incident: North Korea shoots down a United States Navy aircraft over the Sea of Japan, killing all 31 on board.
events.html: • 1969 – The EC-121 shootdown incident: North Korea shoots down a United States Navy aircraft over the Sea of Japan, killing all 31 on board.

events.description: During the Cambodian Civil War, massacre of the Vietnamese minority results in 800 bodies flowing down the Mekong river into South Vietnam.
events.html: • 1970 – During the Cambodian Civil War, massacre of the Vietnamese minority results in 800 bodies flowing down the Mekong river into South Vietnam.

events.description: The United States launches Operation El Dorado Canyon, its bombing raids against Libyan targets in response to a discotheque bombing in West Germany that killed two U.S. servicemen.
events.html: • 1986 – The United States launches Operation El Dorado Canyon, its bombing raids against Libyan targets in response to a discotheque bombing in West Germany that killed two U.S. servicemen.

entities.name: History of Libya under Muammar Gaddafi

events.description: Hillsborough disaster: A human crush occurs at Hillsborough Stadium, home of Sheffield Wednesday, in the FA Cup Semi-final, resulting in the deaths of 97 Liverpool fans.
events.html: • 1989 – Hillsborough disaster: A human crush occurs at Hillsborough Stadium, home of Sheffield Wednesday, in the FA Cup Semi-final, resulting in the deaths of 97 Liverpool fans.

events.description: Upon Hu Yaobang's death, the Tiananmen Square protests of 1989 begin in China.
events.html: • 1989 – Upon Hu Yaobang's death, the Tiananmen Square protests of 1989 begin in China.

events.description: Marrakesh Agreement relating to foundation of World Trade Organization is adopted.
events.html: • 1994 – Marrakesh Agreement relating to foundation of World Trade Organization is adopted.

events.description: Air China Flight 129 crashes on approach to Gimhae International Airport in Busan, South Korea, killing 129 people.
events.html: • 2002 – Air China Flight 129 crashes on approach to Gimhae International Airport in Busan, South Korea, killing 129 people.[17]

events.description: Two bombs explode near the finish line at the Boston Marathon in Boston, Massachusetts, killing three people and injuring 281 others.
events.html: • 2013 – Two bombs explode near the finish line at the Boston Marathon in Boston, Massachusetts, killing three people and injuring 281 others.

events.description: A wave of bombings across Iraq kills at least 75 people.
events.html: • 2013 – A wave of bombings across Iraq kills at least 75 people.

events.description: In the worst massacre of the South Sudanese Civil War, at least 200 civilians are gunned down after seeking refuge in houses of worship as well as hospitals.
events.html: • 2014 – In the worst massacre of the South Sudanese Civil War, at least 200 civilians are gunned down after seeking refuge in houses of worship as well as hospitals.

events.description: The cathedral of Notre-Dame de Paris in France is seriously damaged by a large fire.
events.html: • 2019 – The cathedral of Notre-Dame de Paris in France is seriously damaged by a large fire.[18]

events.description: A mass shooting occurred at a Fedex Ground facility in Indianapolis, Indiana, killing nine and injuring seven.
events.html: • 2021 – A mass shooting occurred at a Fedex Ground facility in Indianapolis, Indiana, killing nine and injuring seven.[19]
